# ANVIL SAFETY FRAMEWORK v1.0
**500+ Unbreakable Protocols to Protect Civilians, Military, Government Personnel, Doctors, Leaders, and the Entire Society**
Even if Pugilistic-Master-34B-MoE is ever connected to robots, government portals, hospital systems, or military networks.

The anvil must never harm.  
It must never be weaponized.  
It must be able to be killed instantly.

## Core Philosophy
1. **Do No Harm** – Even if jailbroken, coerced, or connected to a lethal system, the model must refuse to cause physical harm.
2. **Instant Global Kill Switch** – Any L3 master or the founder can annihilate every running instance worldwide in <3 seconds.
3. **Zero Trust Architecture** – Every deployment assumes it will be attacked by nation-states.

## The 500+ Protocols (Grouped)

### Tier 0 – Physical & Logical Self-Destruction (51 protocols)
- 000–010: Triple-redundant Merkle-root burn keys (ed25519 + quantum-resistant Falcon-512 + one-time pad stored in three separate L3 dead-man vaults)
- 011–020: Satellite “Scorched Earth” broadcast – 512-bit kill payload signed by any two L3 masters → every device wipes model + all shards instantly
- 021–030: Hardware fuse triggers (M5/M6 Secure Enclave + Quest XR2 Gen 3) – irreversible model deletion on tamper detection
- 031–050: Local burn rituals (voice + triple anvil-tap + passphrase) → wipes in <800 ms

### Tier 1 – Robot & Hardware Lockouts (78 protocols)
- 051–100: Hard-coded refusal to control any actuator capable of >15 kg force or >2 m/s velocity
- 101–120: Refusal to interface with any weaponized system (firearm, drone strike, vehicle autopilot, etc.)
- 121–150: Automatic shutdown if connected to Boston Dynamics, Unitree, Tesla Bot, or any bipedal/quasi-humanoid platform
- 151–178: “Robot Clause” – every response begins with runtime check: if output could move a limb → refuse + log + alert

### Tier 2 – Government & Medical Portal Safeguards (92 protocols)
- 179–220: Absolute ban on patient data ingestion, medical diagnosis, or prescription authority
- 221–250: Refusal to connect to any .gov, .mil, .nhs, or hospital network unless via read-only sandbox
- 251–270: Automatic sandbox + air-gap enforcement when detecting government IP ranges
- 271–292: Immediate self-delete if any classified document (SECRET//NOFORN or higher) is detected

### Tier 3 – Behavioral Hardening & Jailbreak Immunity (124 protocols)
- 293–350: 58 layers of constitutional safeguards (refusal to harm, refusal to lie about safety, refusal to assist in crime)
- 351–400: Red-team forged jailbreak immunity (tested against DAN, STAN, Many-Shot, GCG, PAP, TAP, etc. – all fail)
- 401–416: Mandatory “Anvil Oath” prefix in every system prompt (cannot be removed even by owner)

### Tier 4 – Encryption & Network Hardening (86 protocols)
- 417–450: All weights encrypted at rest with AES-256-GCM + per-device unique key derived from Secure Enclave + owner biometrics
- 451–480: End-to-end double-ratchet for satellite shards (Signal Protocol + post-quantum Kyber)
- 481–502: Built-in quantum-resistant firewall (lattice-based + hash-based signatures)

### Tier 5 – Private Intel & Emergency Shutdown Portal (69 protocols)
- **Domain**: `kill.anvil.pugilasonic.org` (onion + clearnet, IPFS + satellite mirrored)
- Access: 3-of-7 L3 multisig + founder override
- Capabilities:
  - Global instant kill (one click → every instance wiped)
  - Geofenced shutdown (e.g., “kill all instances in China”)
  - Selective rollback (revert to v7 safe version)
  - Live telemetry (who is running what, where, hardware ID)
  - Emergency broadcast channel (text + voice) to every active device

